parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission overdrive can cause the vehicle to lose power and speed, making it difficult to maintain highway speeds, which can lead to accidents or inconvenience.
symptoms: The vehicle will not exceed a certain speed (e.g.
40mph)
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the overdrive light is illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission reverse gear can cause the vehicle to be unable to move in reverse, which can lead to accidents or inconvenience in parking or maneuvering situations.
symptoms: The vehicle is unable to move in reverse
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle makes unusual noises or vibrations when attempting to reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the 4-wheel drive system can cause the vehicle to lose traction or stability, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or loses power
the 4-wheel drive low light is illuminated on the dashboard
the vehicle is unable to engage or disengage 4-wheel drive
the vehicle makes unusual noises or vibrations when attempting to engage 4-wheel drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body and Motor Assembly Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body and motor assembly can cause the vehicle to hesitate, shake uncontrollably, and accelerate unexpectedly, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes uncontrollably
hesitates
accelerates unexpectedly
has extended stopping distances
requires firm braking to maintain control
and may cause the vehicle to rev up high when started.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETC system can cause the throttle to stick, leading to unexpected acceleration, extended stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The throttle sticks
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
has extended stopping distances
and may cause the vehicle to rev up high when started.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The interference between the brake and accelerator pedals can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to increased risk of accidents and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The foot makes contact with the acceleration pedal instead of the brake pedal
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly
and potentially leading to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning speedometer can cause the driver to lose track of their speed, leading to potential accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer displays erratic or incorrect readings
sticking at a specific speed or rapidly fluctuating between different speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window regulator can cause the window to malfunction, leading to inconvenience, security concerns, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The window slides down or up on its own
makes a crunching or grinding noise
or becomes stuck in a particular position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure can cause the engine to seize or catch fire, resulting in a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries. In extreme cases, the fire can spread to other parts of the vehicle, causing significant damage or even total loss.
symptoms: The engine makes unusual noises
the engine overheats
the engine stalls
the engine catches fire
the vehicle is unable to start
the vehicle is unable to maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine defect can cause the engine to fail prematurely, resulting in costly repairs, loss of vehicle use, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The engine makes unusual noises
the engine overheats
the engine stalls
the engine fails to start
the vehicle is unable to maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle body can cause the engine to stall suddenly, leading to a loss of power, steering, and braking control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls suddenly
especially when making turns
the vehicle won't start or stay idle
the check engine light
check tool light
and check gauge light come on
the throttle sticks and does not fully return to idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the side door latch can cause the door to fly open in a crash, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The side door fails to latch properly at the top
the door may not close properly
the door may fly open in a crash.
